FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>11/22/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>12:31:48 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.edhughes.net/port/sarez.jpg height=280 width=130 ></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: one more attempt at answers </font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I am going to try and lay this out as plainly as possible for ya Clept.<br>
<br>
First of all, you were labelled a Troll, and flamed because you do not state who you are in game or what guild you are a part of. Is your game name clept? What banner do you wear over your head? You see, while these things may not seem important to you, there have been many trolls who have visited these boards since its inception and the people who use these boards on a regular basis are tired of the flamers, and anonymous posters (trolls). Hence my adverse reaction to you and your post, which felt to be flaming a system you dont seem to uderstand, or even know the origin of. Please tell us who your are. Perhaps I or others have grouped with you in your 200+ levels, and better understand who you are and what your trying to say.<br>
<br>
Secondly. The Calendar system for the Rathe, more commonly known as the RTA, was concieved by yours truly, orginally for KEG, BoTS, CIW, and MFH. The problems they were experiencing between themselves as they vied for position in the High Level Game were not going to be solely their problem forever. So I started the RTA to 1) Create a central location for guilds to post their intent to raid a given plane (orginally you could post intent on dragins and kedge keep as well but Bradan above sated why this was not feasible and hence why those areas/encounters are no longer represented here.), and 2) To pave the way for up and coming guilds to make the transition to the High level game easier. Originally the RTA had no rules whatsoever. Zero. Zilch. None! It was simply a centralized posting spot so raid organizers didnt have to post intent on 5 or 6 different websites.<br>
<br>
As more and more guilds became planes capable though, posting intent was difficult since dates were being reserved 45 days out and more.<br>
<br>
As you can imagine, the intents and dates filled up quickly in such a manner that you couldnt get into a plane for a month or more. At the time the server's guild leadership (Not me or any one single person) got together on these boards and set down some basic rules to follow so that the planes wouldnt be so congested. My job has never been to set policy, but to help enforce it. Much the same way a state legislature creates laws for their respective state, and the police of that state &quot;police&quot; the people using the laws given them. I was the police. Why? Because I was not plane capable at the time and had no bias. Not long after that Aegirson created the calendar to make posting intents easier to read and comprehend. The original process was horribly confusing.<br>
<br>
Things certaintly have changed since then. Weve had rule changes, guild changes, alliance creations, etc etc, but the same premise as always remained the same, and I qoute from the original mision statement...<br>
<br>
&quot;A place for members of The Rathe community to congregate, plan, and organize trips in and around the World of Norrath&quot;<br>
<br>
This isnt a board where a select few guilds set server policy, this is a board that represents 99% of the server population. It is well known, and easily located. Its intents and its scope of power are well outlined.<br>
<br>
No one here is threatening you. No one here says you &quot;cant&quot; do what you want to do. No one here says you &quot;have&quot; to follow the rules and guidelines of this calendar. Yet you do have a responsibility to yourself and your actions. If you break outside the calendar, more power to you, but (and this is not a threat mind you) doing so will be viewed negatively by the 99% of the server who do follow the rules and guidelines here in the spirit of co-operation. What does that mean to you? Only you can answer that question.<br>
<br>
In closing Id like to say that Im sorry you did not know of this sites existance. I have done everything possible to make people aware of it, and as evidence of the representation here, I feel Ive done a good job. We (all the admins, and guild representatives) have done everything we can do to make the resources of this site available to all the inhabitants of the Rathe. The rules and guidelines have been put in place to protect your ability to go to a plane and have an enjoyable experience.<br>
<br>
Now that you know of the sites existance, and its purpose, theres only one question left to ask yourself. When my guild and I are ready to go to the planes, how are we going to proceed?</font><P>Sir Sarel<br>
Knight of Prexus 32nd Circle<br>
Champions of Norrath<br>
